=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_DynKlank_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with saw_like oscillator character around 72 Hz, featuring instant attack and impulsive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: instant
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: impulsive
  envelope_flatness: moderate
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 71.9467
  harmonic_decay_rate: 0.3104
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9575
  pitch_clarity: 15.4159
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: saw_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -7.2915
  resonance_freq: 1119.7266

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: DynKlank Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/DynKlank.html
// Tags: DynKlank, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
{ DynKlank.ar(`[[800, 1071, 1153, 1723], nil, [1, 1, 1, 1]], Impulse.ar(2, 0, 0.1)) }.play;

{ DynKlank.ar(`[[800, 1071, 1353, 1723], nil, [1, 1, 1, 1]], Dust.ar(8, 0.1)) }.play;

{ DynKlank.ar(`[[800, 1071, 1353, 1723], nil, [1, 1, 1, 1]], PinkNoise.ar(0.007)) }.play;

{ DynKlank.ar(`[[200, 671, 1153, 1723], nil, [1, 1, 1, 1]], PinkNoise.ar([0.007, 0.007])) }.play;
